From Germanic ''*launan'', from a suffixed form of Indo-European ''*law-'' ‘catch’. Cognate with Old Frisian [[lan|lān]], Old Saxon [[lon|lōn]] (Dutch [[loon#Dutch|loon]]), Old High German [[lon|lōn]] (German [[Lohn]]), Old Norse [[laun]] (Swedish [[lön]]), Gothic [[𐌻𐌰𐌿𐌽]]. The Indo-European root is also the source of Greek [[λεία]] (from *λαϝία), Latin [[lucrum]], Old Church Slavonic [[ловъ]] (Russian [[лов]]), Old Irish [[lóg]], Lithuanian [[lãvinti]].

